messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path:
  /api/products/top

- all HTTP methods acceptable:
  false

- HEAD:
  false

- POST:
  false

- OPTIONS:
  false

- TRACE:
  false

- GET:
  true

- PUT:
  false

- DELETE:
  false

- PATCH:
  false

Explanation:
- server.js mounts the product router at the prefix /api/products (app.use('/api/products', productRoutes);).
- In routes/productRoutes.js there is an explicit route registration: router.get('/top', getTopProducts); which yields the full path /api/products/top and explicitly accepts the GET method.
- There are no registrations for POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, OPTIONS, TRACE, or HEAD on the /top path in the source (no router.post('/top', ...), router.route('/top'), router.all('/top', ...), or router.head('/top', ...) etc.). Per the instruction to base acceptance on the code (not on framework implicit behaviors), only the explicitly registered GET is considered acceptable.
